# WebJars Support

Beginning with version `1.3.5` the jasmine-maven-plugin supports referencing JavaScript files inside of [WebJars](http://www.webjars.org/) via the [preloadSources](http://searls.github.io/jasmine-maven-plugin/test-mojo.html#preloadSources) configuration parameter.

Example:

```xml
<project>
  ...
  <dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.webjars</groupId>
        <artifactId>jquery</artifactId>
        <version>1.9.0</version>
    </dependency>
  </dependencies>
  <build>
    <plugins>
      <plugin>
        <groupId>${project.groupId}</groupId>
        <artifactId>${project.artifactId}</artifactId>
        <version>${currentStableVersion}<version>
        <executions>
          <execution>
            <goals>
              <goal>test</goal>
            </goals>
          </execution>
        </executions>
        <configuration>
          <preloadSources>
            <source>webjars/jquery.js</source>
          </preloadSources>
        </configuration>
      </plugin>
    </plugins>
  </build>
</project>
```

You can also use a fully qualified reference like this:

Example:

```xml
<project>
  ...
  <dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.webjars</groupId>
        <artifactId>jquery</artifactId>
        <version>1.9.0</version>
    </dependency>
  </dependencies>
  <build>
    <plugins>
      <plugin>
        <groupId>${project.groupId}</groupId>
        <artifactId>${project.artifactId}</artifactId>
        <version>${currentStableVersion}<version>
        <executions>
          <execution>
            <goals>
              <goal>test</goal>
            </goals>
          </execution>
        </executions>
        <configuration>
          <preloadSources>
            <source>webjars/jquery/1.9.0/jquery.js</source>
          </preloadSources>
        </configuration>
      </plugin>
    </plugins>
  </build>
</project>
```
